<dl id="n14232b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14232b">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14232b"> 232(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sign of the hammer / (auctioneer)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;The king then took the drinking horn and made the sign of the cross over it. What does the king mean? said Kaare of Gryting &mdash; Earl Sigurd replied &mdash; He is blessing the full goblet in the name of Thor <mark>by making the sign of his hammer</mark> over it.&rdquo; <small> Charles Haliday, <a name="SKD1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SKD1"><cite title="source">The Scandinavian Kingdom of Dublin</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1884) 125n6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07018c" href="c07all.htm#c07018c">VI.C.07:018(c)</a>, <a name="c07018d" href="c07all.htm#c07018d">VI.C.07:018(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
